# Minimalist Design System Rules

This design system follows minimalist principles with clean typography, subtle shadows, and a cohesive gray color palette. All components should maintain visual consistency and accessibility standards.

## Component Strategy
- Always check shadcn/ui first before creating custom components
- Customize shadcn/ui components by modifying their Tailwind classes
- Preserve accessibility and functionality when customizing
- Only build from scratch if no suitable shadcn/ui component exists

## Color Palette

### Primary Colors
- **Primary**: `text-gray-900`, `bg-gray-900` - Use for main actions and key elements
- **Secondary**: `text-gray-700`, `bg-gray-100` - Use for supporting actions
- **Neutral**: `text-gray-600`, `border-gray-300` - Use for text and subtle backgrounds

### Interactive States
- **Hover**: `hover:bg-gray-800`, `hover:bg-gray-50` - Hover states for interactive elements
- **Focus**: `focus:border-gray-500`, `focus-visible:ring-gray-500` - Focus states for accessibility
- **Disabled**: `text-gray-400`, `opacity-50` - Disabled states

### Status Colors
- **Success**: `bg-emerald-500/10`, `text-emerald-700` - Success states
- **Warning**: `bg-amber-500/10`, `text-amber-700` - Warning states
- **Error**: `bg-red-600`, `border-red-500` - Error and destructive actions
- **Info**: `bg-cyan-500/10`, `text-cyan-700` - Information states

## Typography

### Headings
- **Headings**: Use `font-bold` with consistent size scale (`text-3xl`, `text-2xl`, `text-xl`, `text-lg`)
- **Titles**: Use `font-semibold` for component titles
- **Subtitles**: Use `font-medium` for secondary headings

### Body Text
- **Body text**: Use `font-normal` with proper line height (`leading-relaxed`)
- **UI text**: Use `font-medium` for labels and buttons
- **Small text**: Use `text-xs` for metadata and labels

### Text Hierarchy
- **Primary**: `text-gray-900` - Main content
- **Secondary**: `text-gray-700` - Supporting content  
- **Muted**: `text-gray-600` - Descriptions and labels
- **Placeholder**: `text-gray-500` - Input placeholders

## Spacing Scale

Use consistent spacing: 4px, 8px, 16px, 24px, 32px, 48px
Apply spacing systematically for padding and margins

### Standard Spacing
- **Gap-2** (`gap-2`): 8px - Tight spacing between related elements
- **Gap-3** (`gap-3`): 12px - Standard spacing between elements  
- **Gap-4** (`gap-4`): 16px - Loose spacing between sections
- **Gap-6** (`gap-6`): 24px - Large spacing between major sections

### Component Padding
- **P-2** (`p-2`): 8px - Small padding for compact elements
- **P-3** (`p-3`): 12px - Standard padding for buttons and inputs
- **P-4** (`p-4`): 16px - Medium padding for card headers
- **P-6** (`p-6`): 24px - Large padding for cards
- **P-8** (`p-8`): 32px - Extra large padding for dialogs

## Border Radius

- **Rounded-md** (`rounded-md`): Small elements (buttons, inputs)
- **Rounded-lg** (`rounded-lg`): Standard elements (cards, buttons, inputs)
- **Rounded-xl** (`rounded-xl`): Large elements (dialogs, major containers)

## Shadows

- **Shadow-sm** (`shadow-sm`): Default card shadows
- **Shadow-md** (`shadow-md`): Hover states for cards
- **Shadow-xl** (`shadow-xl`): Modal dialogs and overlays

## Transitions

- **Duration-200** (`duration-200`): Standard transition duration
- **Transition-all** (`transition-all`): For comprehensive changes
- **Transition-colors** (`transition-colors`): For color changes only
- **Transition-shadow** (`transition-shadow`): For shadow changes only
- **Transition-opacity** (`transition-opacity`): For opacity changes only

## Focus States

### Focus Rings
- **Focus-visible:ring-2** (`focus-visible:ring-2`): Standard focus ring
- **Focus-visible:ring-offset-2** (`focus-visible:ring-offset-2`): Ring offset
- **Focus-visible:ring-gray-500** (`focus-visible:ring-gray-500`): Ring color

### Focus Borders
- **Focus:border-gray-500** (`focus:border-gray-500`): Input focus borders
- **Focus:outline-none** (`focus:outline-none`): Remove default outline

## Component Patterns

### Buttons
- **Buttons**: Customize shadcn/ui Button with our color palette
- **Base**: `inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium transition-all duration-200`
- **Primary**: `bg-gray-900 text-white hover:bg-gray-800 focus-visible:ring-gray-500`
- **Secondary**: `bg-gray-100 text-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-200 focus-visible:ring-gray-500`
- **Outline**: `border border-gray-300 bg-white text-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 focus-visible:ring-gray-500`

### Cards
- **Cards**: Use shadcn/ui Card with our shadow and spacing patterns
- **Base**: `bg-white text-gray-900 flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-100 p-6 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow duration-200`
- **Header**: `flex flex-col gap-2 pb-4`
- **Title**: `text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 leading-tight`
- **Content**: `text-gray-700`
- **Footer**: `flex items-center justify-between pt-4 border-t border-gray-100`

### Forms
- **Forms**: Style shadcn/ui Input, Textarea, Select with our design tokens
- **Base**: `flex h-10 w-full rounded-lg border border-gray-300 bg-white px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-900 placeholder:text-gray-500 transition-colors duration-200`
- **Focus**: `focus:border-gray-500 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-gray-500 focus:ring-offset-2`
- **Error**: `aria-invalid:border-red-500 aria-invalid:ring-red-500`

## Accessibility Requirements

### Focus Management
- All interactive elements must have visible focus states
- Use `focus-visible:ring-2` for focus rings
- Include `focus:outline-none` to remove default outlines
- Ensure sufficient color contrast (4.5:1 minimum)

### ARIA Support
- Use `aria-invalid` for form validation states
- Include `sr-only` for screen reader only content
- Maintain proper heading hierarchy
- Use semantic HTML elements

